<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF877677FF3AD2874B3CF3EE" blockId="90.[145,264,1759,1780]" box="[145,264,1759,1780]" pageId="90" pageNumber="507">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF877677FF3AD2874B3CF3EE" box="[145,264,1759,1780]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="507">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF877677FF3AD3404FB6F066" blockId="90.[145,760,1816,1899]" lastBlockId="90.[809,1425,1320,1404]" pageId="90" pageNumber="507">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF877677FF3AD3404AE9F237" box="[145,221,1816,1837]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="507">Males:</emphasis>
This species can be recognized by its slightly elevated PME-bearing region (less elevated then species like 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF877677FE81D30E4BDDF270" authorityName="Lin &amp; Lopardo &amp; Uhl" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Tanasevitch" baseAuthorityYear="2015" box="[298,489,1877,1899]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Mitrager" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="90" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falciferoides">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF877677FE81D30E4BDDF270" box="[298,489,1877,1899]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="507">M. falciferoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D52FF877677FD81D30E4883F270" baseAuthorityName="Tanasevitch" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[554,695,1877,1899]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Mitrager" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="90" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF877677FD81D30E4883F270" box="[554,695,1877,1899]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="507">M. modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the median-long stout setae at the ocular region, and the broad-based, conical palpal tibial prolateral apophysis, which is round at tip and has no enlarged setal base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF877677FC82D1FD4985F0A0" blockId="90.[809,945,1445,1466]" box="[809,945,1445,1466]" pageId="90" pageNumber="507">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF877677FC82D1FD4985F0A0" box="[809,945,1445,1466]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="507">Description:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136D1FF877676FC82D1BB48D1F27B" blockId="90.[809,1426,1507,1897]" lastBlockId="91.[163,780,1438,1890]" lastPageId="91" lastPageNumber="508" pageId="90" pageNumber="507">
<emphasis id="B96AEAC3FF877677FC82D1BB49C4F0E2" box="[809,1008,1507,1528]" italics="true" pageId="90" pageNumber="507">
Male (
<typeStatus id="54A58873FF877677FCDDD1BB49D5F0E2" box="[886,993,1507,1528]" pageId="90" pageNumber="507">paratype</typeStatus>
):
</emphasis>
Total length: 1.95. Prosoma: 0.93 long, 0.75 wide, PME-bearing region slightly elevated, with median-long stout setae at ocular region (
